Because the original multiscale model systematically under-predicted the observed SVR rate in the Synergy trial (see results) we modified the model by distinguishing infectious and non-infectious virus, denoted V
I and V
NI, respectively. We let p
I be the proportion of vRNA assembled and packaged as infectious virus among the total virus released at a given time. We assumed that treatment gradually reduces the amount of infectious virus such that p
I is given by the following equation:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
